olive oil
½ Onion
1 potato
1 packet peeled pumpkin pieces
1 packet Diced Chicken
1 sachet Kiwi Spice Blend
1 packet Baby Leaves
1 packet Dill & Parsley Mayonnaise
1 packet parsley
1 packet haloumi/grill cheese

• Preheat oven to 240°C/220°C fan-forced.
• Cut onion (see ingredients) into quarters.
• Cut potato into bite-sized chunks.
• Place onion, turnip and peeled pumpkin pieces on a lined oven tray. Drizzle with olive oil and season with salt and pepper. Toss to coat, spread out evenly, then roast until tender, 20-25 minutes.

• When the veggies have 10 minutes cook time remaining, heat a large frying pan over high heat with a drizzle of olive oil.
• When oil is hot, cook diced chicken and Kiwi spice blend, turning occasionally, until browned and cooked through, 5-6 minutes.

TIP: Chicken is cooked through when it's no longer pink inside.

• Meanwhile, cut haloumi into 1cm slices.
• In a large frying pan, heat a drizzle of olive oil over medium-high heat. Cook haloumi, until golden brown, 1-2 minutes each side. Transfer to a plate.
• To the tray of roast veggies, add baby leaves and toss to combine.

TIP: Transfer veggies and baby leaves to a bowl if your tray is getting crowded.

• Divide roast pumpkin toss between plates. Top with smokey chicken and haloumi.
• Top with a dollop of dill & parsley mayonnaise and tear over parsley
leaves to serve. Enjoy!